{"article_id":"irIXPriKLOPDYuIA","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"The nurse in Texas seemed to have taken all the precautions","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"needed","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"to protect herself from Ebola .","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"She wore a mask , gown , shield and gloves .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Her patient , a man","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"who contracted the virus in Africa ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"was in isolation at the Dallas hospital","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"where she worked .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"And yet the woman","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"-- whose name has not been released --","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"still contracted Ebola ,","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"marking the first known transmission ever in the United States .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"A nurse in Spain","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"who also treated an Ebola patient","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"also caught the virus .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"She is in critical condition","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"and being treated by 50 health care workers ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"Spanish authorities said Monday .","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention said Sunday","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"there was a breach in protocol in Texas ,","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"but officials have n't elaborated on what that breach was .","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"Instead , they said","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"the protocols","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"laid out for American hospitals work .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"So what happened ?","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"How could a nurse at an American hospital contract the virus ?","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"Is the situation a one-off , an instance of human error , something","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"that probably would n't occur again ?","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"Or could there be more to it ?","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"On Monday morning , an official with direct knowledge of the Texas nurse 's case told CNN","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"that CDC disease detectives have several times interviewed the Texas nurse","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"and think","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"there are `` inconsistencies '' in the type of personal protective gear","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"that she wore","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"and with the process","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"used","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"to put the gear on","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"and remove it .","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"The nurse","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"who tested positive for the virus","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"worked at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital in Dallas .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"CDC Director Dr. Tom Frieden has said","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"the agency is considering several possibilities","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"as to how that breach may have happened ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"including whether the infection was spread","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"when the protective equipment was removed","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"or when the patient , Liberian national Thomas Eric Duncan , received kidney dialysis or respiratory intubation .","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"Those measures were `` a desperate measure","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"to try to save his life , ''","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"Frieden said .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"`` Both of those procedures may spread contaminated materials","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"and are considered high-risk procedures . ''","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"`` When you have potentially soiled or contaminated gloves or masks or other things ,","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"to remove those","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"without any risk of any contaminated material ...","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"touching you","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"and being then on your clothes or face or skin ...","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"is not easy to do right . ''","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"CNN Senior Medical Correspondent Elizabeth Cohen said","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"precautions among health care workers can actually go overboard sometimes .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"The workers are supposed to double their gloves in some situations ,","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"Triple gloving is a violation of CDC protocol","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"and could make things worse .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"`` Then you need to take off three pairs of gloves ...","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"gloves with infectious stuff on them , ''","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"Imagine getting this call about Ebola","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Imagine getting this call about Ebola 01:09","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"`` It is possible in the coming days that we will see additional cases of Ebola , ''","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"Frieden said .","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"That 's because others","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"who provided care to Duncan","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"could have had the same kind of breach as the infected nurse .","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"The official","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"who has direct knowledge of the Texas case","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"told CNN","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"that health authorities will make daily visits to dozens of Dallas health care workers","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"who treated Duncan between September 28 and October 8 at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"The workers have been monitoring their own health ,","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"including taking their own temperature .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"They were previously not considered high risk","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"because they were wearing protective gear ,","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"the official said .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"The CDC is still compiling a list of health care workers","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"who came into contact with Duncan ,","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"the official said .","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"The public areas of the nurse 's apartment complex have been decontaminated","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"and her neighbors have been notified .","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"And the city of Dallas made a reverse-911 call to residents ,","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"notifying them of the city 's second Ebola case .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"`` I think","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"it needs to be put into context that ... you ca n't make an extrapolation","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"that this is now a danger more so to the American people , ''","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"said Dr. Anthony Fauci , director of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases .","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"When a passenger on a flight from New York to Los Angeles fell ill Sunday ,","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"the biggest concern was Ebola .","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"The plane was taken to a remote gate at Los Angeles International Airport .","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"After a few hours , officials determined","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"the woman did not appear to have Ebola ,","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"and other passengers were allowed to leave .","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"And in Louisiana , Attorney General Buddy Caldwell is seeking a temporary restraining order","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"to block the disposal of incinerated waste from Duncan 's personal items at a Louisiana landfill .","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"`` There are too many unknowns at this point ,","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"and it is absurd to transport potentially hazardous Ebola waste across state lines , ''","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"Caldwell said Sunday .","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"Actors aid in Ebola preparations in NYC","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"Actors aid in Ebola preparations in NYC","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"04:06","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":5},{"id":117,"text":"Was euthanizing patient 's dog justified ?","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"Was euthanizing patient 's dog justified ?","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"03:45","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"President Barack Obama wants federal authorities to immediately take further measures","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"to ensure","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"health care workers are able to follow protocols","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"for treating Ebola patients .","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"Of the thousands of hospitals in the United States , only four have been training for years","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"to deal with highly infectious diseases like Ebola :","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"Emory University Hospital in Atlanta , The Nebraska Medical Center , the National Institutes of Health in Maryland , and Rocky Mountain Laboratories in Montana .","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"`` They have the management , the processes , the implementation in place","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"if an Ebola patient comes in ,","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"just right away they know what to do , ''","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"said Gavin MacGregor-Skinner ,","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"who teaches public health preparedness at Penn State University .","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"if someone with symptoms of Ebola shows up at any other hospital ,","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"as Duncan did ,","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"the hospital might not be ready .","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"`` It may not be that every single hospital is in fact prepared for this , ''","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"said David Sanders , associate professor of biology at Purdue University .","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"`` We may have to think about regional centers","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"that are best prepared to deal with Ebola patients . ''","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"On Saturday , passengers","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"arriving from the three countries","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"hardest hit by Ebola","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"started getting special screening ,","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"including having their temperature taken ,","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"at New York 's JFK airport .","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"Washington 's Dulles , Newark , Chicago 's O'Hare and Atlanta international airports will begin screening Thursday .","depth":6},{"id":150,"text":"The country 's largest nursing organization , National Nurses United , surveyed 2,000 members .","depth":6},{"id":151,"text":"Of them , 76 % said","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"their hospital has n't communicated any policy","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"about how to admit Ebola-infected patients .","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"And 85 % said","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"their hospital has n't provided education on Ebola","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"where the nurses can interact","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"and ask questions .","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"Nurses `` are alarmed at the inadequate preparation","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"they see at their hospitals , ''","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"said the group 's executive director , RoseAnn DeMoro .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":321,"left":228,"right":320,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":228,"left":179,"right":227,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":0,"right":178,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":178,"left":172,"right":177,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":168,"right":171,"relation":"adve